			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: white scale<a name="47825"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 23 04 1:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Thousands of bards have managed to complete this quest despite the spawn rates of these dragons and their drop rates of scales. It's supposed to be hard, it's supposed to be a time sink, it's supposed to be a pain in the you-know-what.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The bard epic is most certainly not &quot;supposed&quot; to be how it is now.
<br />

<br />
The game changes, and things that were reasonable before may not be reasonable now.  When the epic quest came out, the cap was 60 and the available gear was complete crap compared to today's standards.  As a result, Gore was a raid level mob.  Raid level mobs have a habit of being up long enough that a person with good help can organize fast enough to kill it.
<br />

<br />
Now, the cap is 65, gear is ridiculous by comparison, and Gore is a mob that can be killed with less than 1 group.  The epic quest was never meant to be bottlenecked by the fact that you had to compete for a mob constantly taken down by a group of 3 wizards, so don't give me any of that &quot;it's supposed to be like this&quot;.
<br />

<br />
People who did their epics back during Kunark/Velious actually had it easier, because the mobs back then stayed up longer, and you could actually find enough people sub 52 for Vox.
<br />

<br />
Right now, the white scale to me is basically &quot;Farm 55k pp&quot; (that's the current lowest cost I've seen in the bazaar on Quellious).  It's not that I don't have the friends to kill Gore, but the odds of finding him still alive are next to nil.  I have no problem with getting a certain piece being too difficult for my capabilities or camped by too many people trying to finish their epic.  I do have a problem when the epic mob is being camped by tons of people who have no interest in the bard epic, forcing me to buy it in the bazaar for ridiculous prices.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
