				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, to satisfy the whiners, let's just issue the epic to newbie bards on character creation.  After all, the difference between watering down a quest a little and watering it down a lot is just one of degree, right?
<br />

<br />
Yes, the game changes.  But if you think Gorenaire lived longer as a raid mob then she does as a one-group kill, you're in a fantasy world.  I can remember my guild mobilizing to kill Gorenaire about 12 times during the period in which we got precisely two kills for our bards.  I don't know how it is on other servers but on Luclin, Gorenaire has NEVER had a lifespan measured in more than an hour or so.  The only difference now is you can kill her with 4 or 5 friends instead of needing 50.  This quest has NOT gotten harder.  Not with people being more mobile, higher level, and better equipped than they ever dreamed of being when I did the quest.  It is absurd to even suggest it's harder than it was before.  These days, you have level 45 bards soloing Maligar because they can buy better gear in the bazaar than my 45 bard could have had in his wildest dreams.  I'm sorry, but it is so much easier to get the epic today, the complaint that we need to make the quest easier is laughable.  It used to be a one year effort requiring not one but a minimum of three full raids.  Now you can get every single piece with a single group of 65s or buy multi-quests of almost all of them.  We have bards litereally EXPECTING the quest to take about a week and bitching if it takes longer.  Yeah, SO much tougher!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
