				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
No one asked for a free epic, oh great and wise satisfied camper of old. 
<br />

<br />
I agree with the above poster that it should test skill, and not patience.  THat's pretty much my complaint about almost all of the quests in EQ, and especially the epics... not bard specific.
<br />

<br />
Give a triggered Gore who only drops the white scale... do some mindless solo (or with friends) collection work on dreadlands mobs... much like triggering Rage in skyfire... so that it will take time... but when the fight comes... it's the same fight that others in the past had to do (easier by today's standards)... but it will test you and your friends, not how much you can camp Gore in the DL... or force yourself not to level hoping to get a Vox raid.
<br />

<br />
Anyone asking for a free epic on dinging 50... or whatever... I don't support.     I do support changing the stupid parts of the quests, to something even slightly more meaningful.    Lets face it... the epic quests aren't epic anymore... and the difficulty is just massively out of whack.
<br />

<br />
For non-raiders especially, the Bard epic still represents great stats.   You can buy better DPS weapons... but as a combination of dps, proc, and pure stats... it's not bad.
<br />

<br />
For all bards... the effect of the instruments is simple amazing.  LDON and AAs have reduced the &quot;need&quot; for it... but it's pretty much a d*mn kick a$ epic for that reason.
<br />

<br />
