<br />

<br />
For myself, it took me over a year and a half to complete mine.  I literally spent 3 and a half months swimming in Kedge Keep hoping to get the jump on Phinny only for him to be the most spinless bastard ever.  I spent another 5 months hanging out almost exclusively in Permafrost until, in my dellusional state, I could almost imagine Vox shouting, &quot;Freaking leave me alone, Gelad!&quot; every time she popped.
<br />

<br />
I have never been in favor of the game being dumbed down or anything being made easier.  I don't mind change, but if the path to gain the scale be made more certain, I think that the path itself should actually be more difficult and dangerous.  The only problem is that the game, in my personal opinion, has already been made too easy and too dumbed down.  And, while Steppy's example of handing out epics to anyone 50+ might be a bit direct, I am quite sure that there are people out there who would actually be in support of this.
<br />

<br />
A few months ago, I had a level 65 beastlord ask me how to get to South Karana.  When I explained it to him, the entire zone had to endure 30 minutes of him ranting over how crappy it was that Sony had not put a PoK book in that zone.  Some people definately just want everything handed to them and will always consider having to work for something as being Sony's way of being unfair.
<br />

<br />
If people want a change to the quest, I hope you get it, but I also dearly hope that they simply give you extra options, but that those extra options be a difficult path to go.  The game is already easy enough.</span></td>
